text: Queen's Day or Koninginnedag was a national holiday in the Kingdom of the Netherlands from 1890 to 2013 that was succeeded by King's Day or Koningsdag. Queen's Day may also refer to: * International Women's Day or Queen's Day * Queen's Official Birthday, a celebration of the birthday of the Queen of the United Kingdom and the other Commonwealth realms * Queene's Day, a celebration of the accession of Queen Elizabeth I
title: Queen's Day (disambiguation)
